# ============================================================
# park.dlg  —  Comprehensive example scene
# One file = one scene/view (the park).
# Each [interaction] is a separate dialogue graph.
# ============================================================

# Scene-wide background defaults.
# Any character listed here gets this bg unless overridden locally.
@bg Merchant  bgAkihiko

== Scene: Riverside Park ==

# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 5 — Merchant with looping/conditional shop flavour
# A travelling merchant has a few things to say; ends with a jump.
# ============================================================

[interaction: merchant_greeting | Travelling merchant near the east gate]

Merchant: Welcome, welcome! Looking for anything in particular?
Merchant: I've got maps, dried goods, and a few... curiosities.

Merchant: What catches your eye?

[choice]
    > What kind of curiosities?  -> @merch_curious
    > Tell me about the maps.    -> @merch_maps
    > Just browsing, thanks.     -> @merch_bye

@merch_curious
Merchant: Ah, a person of taste!
Merchant: I've got a compass that always points to your greatest regret.
Merchant: Terrible for navigation. Wonderful for drama.
Merchant: Interested?

[choice]
    > How much?   -> @merch_price
    > No thanks.  -> @merch_bye

@merch_price
Merchant: For you? Three silver.
Merchant: Or one favour. I'll let you decide which is cheaper.
[end]

@merch_maps
Merchant: Best maps this side of the river!
Merchant: I've got the eastern districts, old town routes, even the underground canals.
Merchant: The canal map's not strictly... legal to own. But that's between us.
[end]

@merch_bye
Merchant: No trouble at all. Come back anytime!
Merchant: I'll be here until the lanterns go out.
[end]
